﻿﻿### MobilityLocation API Tests
### Test file for Rider HTTP Client

### 1. Get all stored locations
GET http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Get only bike locations
GET http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored?type=bike
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get only parking locations
GET http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored?type=parking
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Create a new bike location
POST http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "placeId": "bike_mtl_mcgill",
  "name": "BIXI Station McGill",
  "type": "bike",
  "city": "Montreal",
  "latitude": 45.5048,
  "longitude": -73.5772,
  "capacity": 25,
  "availableSpots": 12
}

###

### 5. Create a new parking location
POST http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "placeId": "parking_mtl_pvm",
  "name": "Place Ville Marie Parking",
  "type": "parking",
  "city": "Montreal",
  "latitude": 45.5017,
  "longitude": -73.5673,
  "capacity": 150,
  "availableSpots": 45
}

###

### 6. Create a bike location in Laval
POST http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "placeId": "bike_lvl_centre",
  "name": "BIXI Station Laval Centre",
  "type": "bike",
  "city": "Laval",
  "latitude": 45.6066,
  "longitude": -73.7124,
  "capacity": 20,
  "availableSpots": 8
}

###

### 7. Get a specific location by ID (replace {id} with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. Update available spots for location ID 1
PATCH http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored/1/spots
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "availableSpots": 18
}

###

### 9. Update available spots for location ID 2
PATCH http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored/2/spots
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "availableSpots": 60
}

###

### 10. Test with invalid data (should return 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "placeId": "",
  "name": "",
  "type": "",
  "city": "Montreal",
  "latitude": 45.5,
  "longitude": -73.6,
  "capacity": 30,
  "availableSpots": 15
}

###

### 11. Get non-existent location (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:5065/api/mobility/stored/99999
Accept: application/json

###
